Task
Create an Array of Interleaved Numbers
Write an alternationArray function that takes a non-negative integer n as an argument and returns an array containing numbers from 0 to n, where even numbers are positive and odd numbers are negative.
Example:
• the alternationArray (5) function must return [0, -1, 2, -3, 4, -5];
• the alternationArray (2) function must return [0, -1, 2];
• the alternationArray (1) function must return [0, -1];
• the alternationArray (0) function must return [0].

Solution
function alternationArray (n) {
 let arr = [];
     for (let i = 0; i <= n; i ++) {
     if (i% 2! == 0)
     arr.push (-i);
      else
     arr.push (i);
     }
     return arr;
}
